---
name: leenk-static
description: Manage the authenticated-write, public-read static file service at yusoofsh.id/static. Use when Codex needs to authenticate the local client, upload or permanently delete HTML, PDF, PNG, or other binary files, choose a nested public path, verify a deployed object with GET or HEAD, or explain how the Leenk R2 static-file endpoint is used.
---

# Leenk Static Files

Use `~/.scripts/leenk-static.sh` as the only upload interface. Do not read, print,
copy, or persist the bearer token outside macOS Keychain.

## Authenticate

Run this only when the user explicitly approves rotating the production upload
credential:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static.sh auth
```

This generates a new token, saves it as the `leenk-static` generic password in
macOS Keychain, and updates the Worker's `STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN` secret. The old
token stops working.

## Upload

Upload to the file's basename:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static.sh upload ./document.pdf
```

Choose a nested public path:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static.sh upload ./report.pdf reports/2026/report.pdf
```

The command prints the public URL on success. Treat uploads as production
publishing: confirm the source file and destination, and do not overwrite an
existing public path unless the user requested it.

## Verify

Inspect metadata without downloading the body:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static.sh head reports/2026/report.pdf
```

Download or open the public URL with ordinary HTTP GET. Public URLs have this
shape:

```text
https://www.yusoofsh.id/static/reports/2026/report.pdf
```

## Delete

Treat deletion as a destructive production action. Require explicit user
approval for the exact remote path before running:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static.sh delete reports/2026/report.pdf
```

The command asks for confirmation. Use `--force` only when the user explicitly
requested non-interactive deletion. Deletion is idempotent: deleting an already
missing path also succeeds.

## Constraints

- Require macOS `security`, `expect`, `openssl`, `curl`, `jq`, and `file`.
- Resolve the Worker project from `LEENK_REPO`, defaulting to
  `~/Developer/Community/leenk`.
- Resolve the public origin from `LEENK_STATIC_ORIGIN`, defaulting to
  `https://www.yusoofsh.id`.
- Never pass the token on the command line or place it in shell history, files,
  logs, skill content, or chat.
- Do not run `auth` merely because an upload or delete fails. Diagnose HTTP and Keychain
  errors first; credential rotation is a production security change.
