     1	# Leenk
     2	
     3	A minimalist personal portfolio for Yusoof Moh, built with Astro and deployed as a Cloudflare Worker.
     4	
     5	## Stack
     6	
     7	- Astro 7 with server-side rendering
     8	- React 19 islands
     9	- Tailwind CSS 4 and typography styles
    10	- Cloudflare Workers through `@astrojs/cloudflare` and Wrangler
    11	- TypeScript 7, Oxlint, Oxfmt, Husky, and lint-staged
    12	- Vite 8 with Rolldown and Vitest 4
    13	- Simple Analytics and a self-hosted Plus Jakarta Sans font
    14	
    15	## Requirements
    16	
    17	- Nub 0.2.10
    18	- Node.js 26.5.0 or newer
    19	
    20	The repository uses Nub's `lock.yaml` as its only package-manager lockfile.
    21	
    22	## Development
    23	
    24	```bash
    25	nub install --frozen-lockfile
    26	nub run dev
    27	```
    28	
    29	The development server is available at <http://localhost:4321> by default.
    30	
    31	## Commands
    32	
    33	| Task                               | Command                |
    34	| ---------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
    35	| Start the Astro development server | `nub run dev`          |
    36	| Build the production Worker        | `nub run build`        |
    37	| Preview through Wrangler           | `nub run preview`      |
    38	| Run the TypeScript check           | `nub run check`        |
    39	| Run unit tests                     | `nub run test`         |
    40	| Run Oxlint                         | `nub run lint`         |
    41	| Check Oxfmt formatting             | `nub run format:check` |
    42	| Check generated Wrangler types     | `nub run types:check`  |
    43	| Run all local verification gates   | `nub run verify`       |
    44	| Apply lint and formatting fixes    | `nub run quality`      |
    45	
    46	Oxfmt formats supported JavaScript, TypeScript, CSS, Markdown, and configuration files. It currently skips `.astro` files, which remain validated by Astro's compiler and production build. CI runs linting, formatting, TypeScript checks, unit tests, the production build, and a high-severity dependency audit.
    47	
    48	## Project Structure
    49	
    50	```text
    51	src/
    52	├── components/        React islands and visual components
    53	├── layouts/           Shared document layout and metadata
    54	├── lib/               Stores and utilities
    55	├── pages/             Astro routes and social redirects
    56	└── styles/            Global Tailwind styles
    57	
    58	public/                Static assets copied into the Worker bundle
    59	wrangler.jsonc         Cloudflare Worker and static-assets configuration
    60	```
    61	
    62	## Static file hosting
    63	
    64	Files uploaded to `/static/<path>` are stored in the `leenk-static` R2 bucket and served directly
    65	from the same URL. Reads are public; uploads and deletes require the `STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN` Worker
    66	secret. Uploads accept a raw request body up to 100 MiB.
    67	
    68	Create the R2 bucket and upload secret once before the first deployment:
    69	
    70	```bash
    71	nub exec wrangler r2 bucket create leenk-static
    72	nub exec wrangler secret put STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN
    73	```
    74	
    75	Upload any binary file while preserving its media type:
    76	
    77	```bash
    78	printf 'header = "Authorization: Bearer %s"\n' "$STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN" | \
    79	  curl --config - https://www.yusoofsh.id/static/docs/guide.pdf \
    80	    -X POST \
    81	    -H "Content-Type: application/pdf" \
    82	    --data-binary @guide.pdf
    83	```
    84	
    85	The same URL supports public `GET` and `HEAD`. Uploading the same path again replaces the existing
    86	file. Authenticated deletion is idempotent and returns `204 No Content`:
    87	
    88	```bash
    89	printf 'header = "Authorization: Bearer %s"\n' "$STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN" | \
    90	  curl --config - https://www.yusoofsh.id/static/docs/guide.pdf \
    91	    -X DELETE \
    92	    -H "Content-Type: application/octet-stream"
    93	```
    94	
    95	## Deployment
    96	
    97	The build produces an Astro server entry point and static assets in `dist/`. Preview the exact Worker configuration locally before deploying:
    98	
    99	```bash
   100	nub run build
   101	nub run preview
   102	```
   103	
   104	Production deployment is intentionally explicit:
   105	
   106	```bash
   107	nub run deploy
   108	```
   109	
   110	Deploy only after local and CI verification pass. The deploy command changes production state and requires separate approval when run by an agent.
   111	
   112	## Contributing
   113	
   114	1. Create a short-lived branch.
   115	2. Make a focused change.
   116	3. Run `nub run verify`.
   117	4. Commit with a conventional commit message.
   118	5. Open a pull request and wait for CI.
   119	
   120	## Security
   121	
   122	Report vulnerabilities privately using the process in [SECURITY.md](SECURITY.md).
   123	
   124	## License
   125	
